  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators attempted to determine the optimal dose of dexmedetomidine required for the
      successful insertion of LMA during propofol induction without a neuromuscular blocking agent.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      After a predetermined bolus dose of dexmedetomidine was injected over 2 min, anesthesia was
      induced with propofol 2.0 mg/kg. After confirming the loss of eyelash reflex and the
      bispectral index (BIS) score decreased below 60, the insertion of LMA was attempted.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
